    "summary": "www.CMCMaastricht.nl\n\nBen Willems, M.S., L.Ac. studied acupuncture and herbology at Yo San University and at Atlantic University of Chinese Medicine. He obtained his Master\u2019s level degree in 2006.\n\nBen received his Master\u2019s degree in Environmental Health Sciences from the University of Maastricht, the Netherlands in 1995. From 1995 to 1997 Ben worked as a scientist in both Australia and the Netherlands on skin-cancer research. In 1997 he moved to the United States and worked as a fellow-scientist for the U.S. National Institute of Environmental Health Sciences on the relationship between hormone levels and breast-cancer development in women. During his years in the scientific field he has published several articles in peer-reviewed journals and wrote a chapter in a handbook on Environmental Health. However, as the years went by his interest shifted towards Traditional Chinese Medicine and decided to pursue a degree in TCM. Ben was a faculty member at Yo San University, Emperors College (both in Los Angeles, CA), Atlantic University of Chinese Medicine (Mars Hill, NC) and Daoist Traditions University (Asheville, NC). He also had a private practice in Asheville, NC until moving back to the Netherlands in the Spring of 2010.\n\nAfter working as a therapist at the U-center in Epen, the Netherlands, Ben now runs Chinese Medical Center Maastricht. A clinic for Traditional Chinese Medicine. He also organizes Mindfulness and Qi Gong courses.\n\n\nSpecializing in pain relief, circulatory issues, digestive problems, mental/emotional imbalances, stress, burnout and cancer care.\n\nSpecialties: acupuncture, herbal medicine, Mindfulness, cancer research, epidemiology, toxicology",
